Mxolisi Mngadi It is a terrible weekend on our roads, with many fatal accidents already reported and more expected. Durban – A six-year-old boy is fighting for his life in hospital following Sunday night’s fatal accident which claimed seven lives on the R617 in Underberg, KwaZulu-Natal. The seven people who died at the scene were in a light motor vehicle which collided with a truck about 21:25, police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said on Monday. The deceased are believed to be from one family. "The six-year-old boy was taken to hospital, where he is reported to be in a critical condition. The circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated," Gwala said. The truck driver was also injured in the accident. A case of culpable homicide was being investigated by the Himeville police, she said. Meanwhile, five people were killed and three others injured in a head-on collision between a BMW and a Toyota Corolla on the N3 highway in Van Reenen, KwaZulu-Natal, also on Sunday afternoon. ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said the incident happened at 16:15. A boy, believed to be 11 years old, was among the three injured occupants of the BMW, said Siddall. The deceased were occupants of the Toyota Corolla. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  